<div id="review_7062985" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/7062985" />
    <a title="Febry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/437893-febry"><img alt="Febry" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/7062985?book_show_action=true">Sep 30, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Febry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Febry" href="/user/show/437893-febry">Febry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">everyone  (except for kids under 15 years old, i think)</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7062985" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4116083629796140738">The book reached number 1 on Border&apos;s, Washington Post, and Boston Globe best seller lists, and also New York Times Best Seller List. The genre is fictional mystery.<br/><br/><br/>This book has a strong relation with Dante&apos;s DIVINA COMEDIA (Divine Comedy).<br/><br/>You don&apos;t have to read the Divine Comedy first in order to understand this novel. But if you do already read Divine Comedy, it&apos;s very good, because you can have deep understanding about what is DANTE all about.<br/><br/>This novel is about a killer that doing his/her (</span>
  <span id="freeText4116083629796140738" style="display:none">The book reached number 1 on Border's, Washington Post, and Boston Globe best seller lists, and also New York Times Best Seller List. The genre is fictional mystery.<br /><br /><br />This book has a strong relation with Dante's DIVINA COMEDIA (Divine Comedy).<br /><br />You don't have to read the Divine Comedy first in order to understand this novel. But if you do already read Divine Comedy, it's very good, because you can have deep understanding about what is DANTE all about.<br /><br />This novel is about a killer that doing his/her (you have to find out yourself) ^_^ murders according to what is written in Divine Comedy.<br /><br />There's a group of people that translating the Divine Comedy from italian language to english, the group were called Dante's Club.<br />As they translate the Divine Comedy, the murders also happend and that makes the group think that all the murders that are heppening has something to do with the group activity on translating the Divine Comedy.<br /><br />So as the police investigate the murders, the Dante's club also make their own investigation.<br /><br />That's where the FUN begginssssss........<br /><br />The caharacters of Dante's club member are based on real people, and all of them has strong personality.<br /><br />From wikipedia:<br />"The plot is largely fictional, although the main characters are real, as are many of their biographical details. Supporting and background characters, as well as those directly involved with the murders, are also mostly fictional."<br /><br />Quite descriptive, the writer is Matthew Pearl and this book already get much good reviews.<br /><br />You guys must read this one.<br /><br />------<br />Febry<br />------</span>
  <a data-text-id="4116083629796140738" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


